&gt; I don&#39;t know which connection pool you on about but I know how my own
&gt; connection pool works.  When a connection is returned it checks the
&gt; transaction and rolls it back it one is open &quot;SELECT @@trancount&quot; on SQL
&gt; Server.  This also serves the purpose of making sure the connection is OK,
&gt; i.e. no network cables pulled out etc.  If the connection is working then
&gt; its put back in the pool.  If the connection is faulty then it is closed
and
&gt; removed from the pool.
&gt;
&gt; Not sure how you make sure all connections are returned.  Could do with a
&gt; way to signal all sub-systems to return any connections and then check
that
&gt; none are still checked out of the pool.
&gt;
&gt; Dave
